**Title:** COM - LockPick Community - SAINTCON

**URL:** [LockPick Community](https://saintcon.org/com-lockpick-community/)

**Overview:**
The LockPick Community at SAINTCON aims to foster a security mindset and develop critical thinking through lock picking. It offers hands-on classes and utilizes a martial arts belt system to guide participants from novice to expert.

**Key Features:**
- **Learning Path:** 
  - Beginner to Expert progression.
  - Hands-on classes for skill acquisition.
  - Structured belt system for skill advancement.
  
- **Provided Equipment:**
  - Essential tools and locks for starters.
  - Personal lockpicking sets recommended for more advanced learners.

**FAQs:**
- **Belt System:** Relies on the Lock Pickers United system, allowing participants to earn micro-badge belts at SAINTCON.
- **More Info on Belts:** Visit [lpubelts.com](http://lpubelts.com).

**Getting Involved:**
Open to beginners and experienced lock pickers. The community encourages all interested to join.

**Hours of Operation:**
- Monday: Expo Closed
- Tuesday: 10:30 AM - 5:00 PM
- Wednesday: 10:30 AM - 5:00 PM
- Thursday: 9:00 AM - 5:00 PM
- Friday: 9:00 AM - 11:00 AM

**What You'll Learn:**
- How lock systems work and their vulnerabilities.
- Techniques for picking standard and advanced locks.

**MiniBadge Details:**
Collect a community MiniBadge by visiting the booth for more information.

